summary: Oxford United Football Club, nicknamed The U's, is a professional soccer team from Oxford, England. They play in the second-highest league in England, the EFL Championship, after winning the 2024 EFL League One play-off final. The club was founded in 1893 and has had many ups and downs, including winning the League Cup in 1986 but also getting relegated to the Conference in 2006. They wear yellow shirts with navy shorts and socks. Oxford has a strong rivalry with Swindon Town, playing the A420 derby.
title: Oxford United F.C.
